Code Management and Future Update Checklist

This page provides an overview of the code files used in the sweep impact analysis, along with a checklist for future updates. This guide will help new team members locate and understand the code required for each step of the process.

Code Repository

Our repository is in Bitbucket and includes the following files essential for the sweep impact analysis:

1. sweep.pipeline.R

	•	Functionality:
	•	Data Extraction: Reads extracted data from the open_RL.sql query.
	•	Data Preparation: Prepares data for scoring.
	•	Model Scoring: Scores the data once using model v2 and again using model v3.
	•	Exposure List Creation: Creates a list of exposures for IT.
	•	Dataset Preparation:
	•	Creates the dataset for the pre-sweep report.
	•	Prepares the final dataset for the real sweep impact by reading data extracted from logs.

2. sweep_impact.rmd

	•	Functionality: Creates the sweep impact report.
	•	Usage:
	•	This file is used for both the pre-sweep report and the real sweep impact report. The only difference is the input dataset used.

3. sweep_error.R

	•	Functionality: Used for data validation by comparing CIM data with logs.
	•	Purpose:
	•	Identifies mismatches in predicted reserves.
	•	Detects variable mismatches for each row of data for each Reserve Line (RL).

Future Update Checklist

This checklist provides steps to update the code files as necessary for future analyses.

1. sweep.pipeline.R Updates

	•	Verify Data Extraction: Ensure that the open_RL.sql query is up to date with any changes to the data required for analysis.
	•	Model Scoring Adjustments: If model v2 or v3 is updated, confirm that scoring adjustments are reflected in the code.
	•	Exposure List Creation: Check that the exposure list generation aligns with IT’s requirements.
	•	Dataset Preparation for Reports: Ensure the datasets for both the pre-sweep and real sweep impact reports are correctly structured.

2. sweep_impact.rmd Updates

	•	Report Structure: Confirm that the report structure meets current requirements.
	•	Input Dataset: Verify that the correct input dataset is used for either the pre-sweep or real sweep impact report.

3. sweep_error.R Updates

	•	Comparison Logic: Update the comparison logic if there are changes in CIM data fields or logging formats.
	•	Discrepancy Identification: Ensure all relevant discrepancies in predicted reserves and variables are flagged.

This page provides a quick reference for managing and updating the code files related to the sweep impact analysis, ensuring consistency and accuracy for future runs.